  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_d8650c6ca13ea6c10e79fa94ec2d1ebb">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Photographs of ancient Egyptian monuments, temples, and carvings, as well and papyri and artifacts. Also includes images of Heidelberg and unidentified German buildings.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite audience="internal" id="aspace_87632624f2d2fde65cb82f2cb7d6e719">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>August Eisenlohr photographs of Egypt, #6779. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_0f0497ba2347f4bdf05b94d0688d2c24">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>German Egyptologist.</p>  </bioghist>
  <arrangement audience="internal" id="aspace_f936a2c223c24414f36bea4804c03680">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>The photographs in this collection were assigned different numbers, possibly by Eisenlohr, but no list of photographs and numbers exists. The photographs have been organized according to this numbering system.</p>  </arrangement>
